<subSubSection pageId="101" pageNumber="102" type="discussion">
<paragraph blockId="101.[151,1436,759,1072]" pageId="101" pageNumber="102">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[199,273,796,821]" pageId="101" pageNumber="102">Notes.</emphasis>
A single specimen record confirmed by S. Droege and examination of photographs. 
<bibRefCitation author="Fye" box="[1306,1436,796,821]" firstAuthor="Fye" pageId="101" pageNumber="102" pagination="863 - 877" refId="ref87906" refString="Fye, R. E. (1965) Biology of Apoidea taken in trap nests in northwestern Ontario (Hymenoptera). The Canadian Entomologist, 97, 863 - 877. https: // doi. org / 10.4039 / ent 97863 - 8" type="journal article" year="1965">Fye (1965)</bibRefCitation>
recorded this species from Black Sturgeon Lake, Ontario; approximately 
<quantity box="[1027,1119,831,856]" metricMagnitude="5" metricUnit="m" metricValue="1.25" pageId="101" pageNumber="102" unit="km" value="125.0">125 km</quantity>
north of Isle Royale as a cleptoparasite of 
<taxonomicName baseAuthorityName="Provancher" baseAuthorityYear="1888" box="[349,539,868,893]" class="Insecta" family="Megachilidae" genus="Hoplitis" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hymenoptera" pageId="101" pageNumber="102" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="spoliata">
<emphasis box="[349,539,868,893]" italics="true" pageId="101" pageNumber="102">Hoplitis spoliata</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
(see also 
<bibRefCitation author="Sheffield" box="[658,899,868,893]" etAl="et al." firstAuthor="Sheffield" pageId="101" pageNumber="102" pagination="235 - 249" refId="ref102385" refString="Sheffield, C. S., Kevan, P. G., Westby, S. M. &amp; Smith, R. F. (2008) Diversity of cavity-nesting bees (Hymenoptera: Apoidea) within apple orchards and wild habitats in the Annapolis Valley, Nova Scotia, Canada. The Canadian Entomologist, 140, 235 - 249. https: // doi. org / 10.4039 / n 07 - 058" type="journal article" year="2008">
Sheffield 
<emphasis box="[770,829,868,893]" italics="true" pageId="101" pageNumber="102">et al.</emphasis>
2008
</bibRefCitation>
). 
<bibRefCitation author="Graenicher" box="[920,1129,868,893]" firstAuthor="Graenicher" pageId="101" pageNumber="102" pagination="285 - 310" refId="ref89639" refString="Graenicher, S. (1935) Bee-fauna and vegetation of Wisconsin. Annals of the Entomological Society of America, 28, 285 - 310. https: // doi. org / 10.1093 / aesa / 28.2.285" type="journal article" year="1935">Graenicher (1935)</bibRefCitation>
recorded it from a nest of 
<taxonomicName authority="Smith" authorityName="Smith" authorityYear="1853" box="[151,413,903,928]" class="Insecta" family="Megachilidae" genus="Osmia" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hymenoptera" pageId="101" pageNumber="102" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="simillima">
<emphasis box="[151,337,903,928]" italics="true" pageId="101" pageNumber="102">Osmia simillima</emphasis>
Smith
</taxonomicName>
from Milwaukee, Wisconsin on the shore of Lake Michigan, but his identification might apply to 
<taxonomicName authority="(Medler &amp; Lussenhop 1968)" authorityName="Medler &amp; Lussenhop" authorityYear="1968" baseAuthorityName="Medler &amp; Lussenhop" baseAuthorityYear="1968" box="[249,724,940,965]" class="Insecta" family="Megachilidae" genus="Stelis" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hymenoptera" pageId="101" pageNumber="102" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="labiata">
<emphasis box="[249,395,940,965]" italics="true" pageId="101" pageNumber="102">Stelis labiata</emphasis>
(
<bibRefCitation author="Medler &amp; Lussenhop" box="[409,716,940,965]" firstAuthor="Medler" pageId="101" pageNumber="102" pagination="1 - 80" refId="ref94805" refString="Medler, J. T. &amp; Lussenhop, J. F. (1968) Leafcutter bees of Wisconsin. University of Wisconsin Research Bulletin, 274, 1 - 80." type="journal article" year="1968">Medler &amp; Lussenhop 1968</bibRefCitation>
)
</taxonomicName>
.
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="101.[151,1436,759,1072]" box="[199,880,975,1000]" pageId="101" pageNumber="102">
Recorded as a cleptoparasite of 
<taxonomicName baseAuthorityName="Provancher" baseAuthorityYear="1888" box="[556,680,975,1000]" class="Insecta" family="Megachilidae" genus="Hoplitis" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hymenoptera" pageId="101" pageNumber="102" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="spoliata">
<emphasis box="[556,576,977,1000]" italics="true" pageId="101" pageNumber="102">H</emphasis>
